NORTH WEST PROVINCIAL MINING AND ENERGY INVESTMENT CONFERENCE Date: 25-26 January 2022 Bon HotelRUSTENBURG The North West Mining and Energy Investment Conference is hosted by The Department of Mineral Resources and Energy. The Department of Mineral Resources and Energy cordially invites you to save the date for the North West mining and energy investment conference. The North West is known as South Africa’s ‘Platinum Province’ due to its abundant mineral riches of platinum, chrome and the platinum group metals. It is also home to a strong dimension stone sector, due to the riches of its slate, marble and granite deposits. Taking place 25-26 January 2022, the conference will focus on the diverse investment opportunities in the North West, highlight and promote junior mining, and enhance social cohesion and post-Covid 19 economic recovery. Attendees have the option to participate in person at the Bon Hotel, Rustenburg, North West or digitally through our digital conference platform. THE OBJECTIVES OF THE CONFERENCE ARE TO: DAY 1: 25th January 2022 Programme Director: Director General/Administrator, North West Province DAY 2: 26th January 2022